2MASS All-Sky Point Source Catalog 1.description:
2MASS has uniformly scanned the entire sky in three near-infrared bands to detect and characterize point sources brighter than about 1 mJy in each band, with signal-to-noise ratio (SNR) greater than 1.

This particular record describes access to the position-based catalog data in this collection through the VO-standard ConeSearch service interface.  It can be used automatically by compliant tools and applications.
